Terraform + GitHub Troubleshooting Notes
Errors Faced During Terraform AWS VPC Project

This document contains practical troubleshooting scenarios faced while building and pushing the Terraform AWS VPC project to GitHub.

These are real-world issues commonly faced by Cloud/DevOps engineers.

1. EC2 SSH Permission Denied Error
Error
ec2-user@10.0.11.242: Permission denied (publickey,gssapi-keyex,gssapi-with-mic)
Cause

Connected from Bastion Host to private EC2 without providing the SSH private key.

The bastion server did not contain the PEM key required for authentication.

Solution

Copied PEM key to Bastion Host using:

scp -i terraform-key.pem terraform-key.pem ec2-user@<BASTION_PUBLIC_IP>:/home/ec2-user/

Set correct permissions:

chmod 400 terraform-key.pem

Connected again:

ssh -i terraform-key.pem ec2-user@10.0.11.242
Learning
Bastion host acts as jump server
Private instances require proper SSH authentication
SSH keys need correct permissions
Common enterprise access pattern
2. DynamoDB Billing Mode Error
Error
billing_mode = "PAY-PER-REQUEST"

Terraform validation failed.

Cause

Incorrect billing mode format used.

Terraform expects underscore (_) instead of hyphen (-).

Solution

Corrected to:

billing_mode = "PAY_PER_REQUEST"
Learning

Terraform values are case-sensitive and syntax-sensitive.

3. DynamoDB Attribute Type Error
Error
expected type to be one of ["S" "N" "B"], got s
Cause

Used lowercase "s" instead of uppercase "S" for DynamoDB attribute type.

Solution

Corrected:

type = "S"
Learning

DynamoDB supports:

"S" → String
"N" → Number
"B" → Binary

Values are case-sensitive.

4. S3 Bucket Already Exists Error
Error
BucketAlreadyExists
Cause

S3 bucket names are globally unique across all AWS accounts.

The bucket name was already taken.

Solution

Changed bucket name to unique value:

bucket = "aaru-terraform-backend-2026-001"
Learning

S3 bucket namespace is global.

Always use unique naming convention:

project name
environment
random number/year
5. Terraform Backend Region Mismatch Error
Error
requested bucket from "ap-south-1", actual location "us-east-1"
Cause

Terraform backend region did not match actual S3 bucket region.

Solution

Updated backend configuration:

region = "us-east-1"

Reinitialized backend:

terraform init -reconfigure
Learning

Terraform backend region must match S3 bucket region.

6. GitHub Password Authentication Failed
Error
Password authentication is not supported for Git operations
Cause

GitHub no longer supports username/password authentication for Git operations over HTTPS.

Solution

Generated GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT).

Used:

GitHub username
PAT instead of password
Learning

Modern GitHub authentication uses:

PAT
SSH keys

instead of passwords.

7. GitHub 403 Permission Denied Error
Error
Permission denied to repository
Cause

Token lacked proper repository permissions OR old credentials were cached.

Solution
Generated new token with:
repo

permission enabled.

Cleared old credentials from Windows Credential Manager.
Learning

PAT must contain required scopes.

8. Large File Upload Error
Error
terraform-provider-aws.exe exceeds GitHub file size limit
Cause

.terraform/ directory was accidentally committed to Git repository.

This folder contains huge provider binaries.

Solution

Created .gitignore:

.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*
*.pem
terraform.tfvars

Removed Git history and reinitialized repository:

Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .git
git init
Learning

Never upload:

.terraform/
.tfstate
.pem
secrets

Terraform automatically downloads providers during:

terraform init
9. Confusion Between VS Code and PowerShell
Issue

Confusion regarding:

where to write code
where to run commands
Clarification
Tool	Purpose
VS Code	Write/edit files
PowerShell Terminal	Run Terraform/Git commands
Learning

Standard DevOps workflow:

VS Code → Write Code
Terminal → Run Commands
GitHub → Store Code
